CommonJS is a module system used in JavaScript, mainly for Node.js.

It allows you to import and export code (functions, variables, etc.) between files.

Syntax

Import (require)

const math = require("./math");


Export (module.exports)

module.exports = add;

One-line MCQ answer

CommonJS is a JavaScript module standard used mainly in Node.js where modules are loaded using require() and exported using module.exports.


